node.text:
While at Hillcrest Elementary, I met one of my first mentors, @shblonde_bomb. We met at LA’s Best After School Program where she coached the schools Drill Team. Shanora allowed me to practice with the older girls at Inglewood High School. Being around these ladies and Shanora had me soaking in all the knowledge and confidence I needed to get out there. I look back now at the importance of this experience. Not only was I embarking on this journey in Drill, but also outside of it.
📷 @sureshgordon @jumpman23 
👯‍♀️ @xoxo.moraaa_ @aniyahquianaa__
@hairbyess @sage.white

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Aleali (uh•lay•lee) on August 10, 2021 tagging @captainbarlos, @jumpman23, @iammontechristo, @sashaelina, @burrbrii, @shotbykvng, @tylradams, @sureshgordon, and @cloudnai. May be an image of 3 people and indoor.

node.text:
The idea that an AJ14 @jumpman23 model is based on fast cars and luxury… 
I thought as women many luxury pieces for us, is jewelry. Then I thought, what was the first piece of jewelry I had? 
Both my grandmothers gifted me with Jade💚 
Granny on my dads side always taught me to be independent. She was born & raised in South Central,LA. She was one of the first classes to attend Crenshaw High. Matter of fact, that famous blue and gold Crenshaw color way.. her class voted on those colors💙💛 She worked at many banks and later opened a daycare, still running today in SC, LA. 
My Lola(grandma), Born in the Philippines - a place called Laguna, and later moved to Makati in Manila. Her older sister, Great Tita(Aunt) Sue who I had shoot for this campaign, told the family, “Let’s move to America!” Teaching me to take risks, My grandma followed her older sister. Tita Sue started teaching grade school and still does today. 
Like many of us, there’s definitely a theme of strong women in the family. So I had to highlight these special Queens that helped raise me and the Jade pieces they passed down to me💚
Global Launch 🌎 August 19

node.text:
Blessed to be able to bring in my Birthday today with another special project @jumpman23 featuring two of my fav Queens, Granny & Great Tita(Aunt) Sue🖤
My drive is a product of the many pieces of my identity. It’s like basketball or any other sport—in order to win, you have to play multiple roles, often having to shift between those roles at a moment's notice. Women have to do that every day. We’re mothers, sisters, daughters, and friends. We’re bosses and teachers and designers and athletes and scientists and group chat comedians. Our identity isn’t just formed by what we wear, but by the actions we take. It’s based on how we live, and the environments we create. 
Mimi (Tita Sue) and Granny showed me essential pieces of my identity. 
Stay down.. never forgetting where you came from. 
Stay consistent.. charging forwards, no matter what the roadblocks. 
Stay loyal..being true to who you are; becoming the person your younger self dreamed of✨

The “FORTUNE” XIV 
August 19, 2021🌎GLOBAL
